claim.claim-text:
1. A constant voltage (CV) welding process power supply comprising:
a control circuit that, in operation:
computes a varying minimum current level during a welding process;
computes, during the welding process, a voltage error between an instantaneous welding voltage level of the welding process and a desired voltage level;
generates a current command signal to minimize the computed voltage error;
compares the current command signal to the computed varying minimum current level; and
applies either the current command signal or the computed varying minimum current level for control of welding output based upon the comparison.
